ivardefs.name: additionalCharacteristic_
ivardefs.desc: Used for examplefor Out of Formulary, or any specifics.

ivardefs.name: additionalClassification_
ivardefs.desc: User for example for ATC classification, or.

ivardefs.name: additionalIdentifier_
ivardefs.desc: Used in supporting related concepts, e.g. NDC to RxNorm.

ivardefs.name: classification_
ivardefs.desc: Classes of devices, or ATC for medication.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: Used in supporting different identifiers for the same product, e.g. manufacturer code and retailer code.

ivardefs.name: lastUpdated
ivardefs.desc: Typically date of issue is different from the beginning of the validity. This can be used to see when an item was last updated.

ivardefs.name: orderable
ivardefs.desc: Whether the entry represents an orderable item.

ivardefs.name: referencedItem
ivardefs.desc: The item in a catalog or definition.

ivardefs.name: relatedEntry_
ivardefs.desc: Used for example, to point to a substance, or to a device used to administer a medication.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: Used to support catalog exchange even for unsupported products, e.g. getting list of medications even if not prescribable.

ivardefs.name: type
ivardefs.desc: The type of item - medication, device, service, protocol or other.

ivardefs.name: validityPeriod
ivardefs.desc: The time period in which this catalog entry is expected to be active.

ivardefs.name: validTo
ivardefs.desc: The date until which this catalog entry is expected to be active.

properties.desc: Catalog entries are wrappers that contextualize items included in a catalog.
